"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-tommy-fleetwood-scottie-scheffler-golf-b1174677.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  Team GB'sTommy Fleetwoodwon silver asScottie Schefflerwas crowned Olympic men's champion atParis 2024.  Fleetwood fired a final-day 66 to finish one stroke short of Scheffler's 19-under-par total after the world No1 had tied the LeGolfNational course record with a 62.  The 33-year-old from Southport was level with USA's Scheffler with two holes to play, but a bogey on the 17th cost him dear.  Scheffler produced six birdies in his back-nine 29 to add to the multiple titles he has won on the PGA Tour this year, including hissecond Masters title at Augusta in April.  Hideki Matsuyama, of Japan, finished one shot behind Fleetwood to take bronze with France's Victor Perez fourth after the home favourite had come home in 29.  Ireland's Rory McIlroy was tied fifth with Jon Rahm after finding his best form of the week.  McIlroy thrust himself into medal contention with five successive birdies in the back nine, but finished two shots behind Matsuyama after finding water at 15 and taking a double bogey six.  Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions  Incredible days out and trips for autumn and winter  Rahm held a four-shot lead walking off the 10th green, but the Spaniard's hopes unravelled with a disastrous back nine of 39.  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"